main event: A bright, circular object was observed hovering over the trees in Newburgh, New York on April 7, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as very bright and glowing.
The witness attempted to take a photograph of the object, but it did not come out.
The object was observed for approximately 5 minutes.
The observation occurred at 7:45 PM on a clear night sky.
No other actions were reported to be taken.
photographs: yes, but the photograph did not come out
